{"id":158,"parent_id":157,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":158,"title":"2 Timothy 1-2: Endure Hardness","subtitle":"","short_title":"2 Timothy 1-2: Endure Hardness","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness"},[".heading",{"id":"head2","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness.head2"},["h1","2Timothy 1–2"],[".subtitle","Endure Hardness"],[".intro","Do you know anyone involved in the military, sports, farming, or ranching? As you read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-tim/1"},"2 Timothy 1–2"],", notice how Paul compared living the gospel to a war, an athletic contest, and the harvesting of crops. Why do you think Paul used these comparisons?"]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness.f1"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-tim/1"},"2 Timothy 1"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Unfeigned"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Sincere"],["td"]]]]],[".figure",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness.f2"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-tim/2"},"2 Timothy 2"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Husbandman"],"(v. 6)"],["td","Farmer, land worker"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Charging"],"(v. 14)"],["td","Commanding"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Subverting"],"(v. 14)"],["td","Destruction, ruin"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Erred"],"(v. 18)"],["td","Been in error"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Gender"],"(v. 23)"],["td","Bring about or cause"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness.p8"},"Do activity A or B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-tim/1"},"2 Timothy 1–2"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Spiritual Soldiers, Athletes, and Farmers"],[".figure",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness.f3"},["p.preamble","Make three columns in your notebook and label them with the words",["span.emphasis","Soldier, Athlete,"],"and",["span.emphasis","Farmer."]],["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-tim/2.1-6"},"2 Timothy 2:1–6"],"and list in the columns what each person is to do (for example, the soldier is to “endure hardness”)."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Write a paragraph describing why you think soldiers, athletes, and farmers are good comparisons to use in a talk about developing spirituality."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"In Your Own Words"],["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-timothy/2-timothy-1-2-endure-hardness.p11"},"Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-tim/2.22-26"},"2 Timothy 2:22–26"],"and write a short paragraph explaining why you think these verses are important to you today."]]]]]]],"refs":null}
